Simpsh

Simple shell script

Users invoke shell script by passing arguments telling which files to access, which pipes to create, and which commands to invoke.
Options to script arguments are passed as long options, whereas arguments to subcommands are passed as they would be in terminal.
The below are supported options for simpsh:

File flags:
--append
  O_APPEND
--cloexec
  O_CLOEXEC
--creat
  O_CREAT
--directory
  O_DIRECTORY
--dsync
  O_DSYNC
--excl
  O_EXCL
--nofollow
  O_NOFOLLOW
--nonblock
  O_NONBLOCK
--rsync
  O_RSYNC
--sync
  O_SYNC
--trunc
  O_TRUNC

File opening options:
--rdonly file
  O_RDONLY
--rdwr file
  O_RDWR
--wronly file
  O_WRONLY
--pipe

Subcommand options:
--command i o e cmd args
  //i is input file, o is output file, e is stderr.
--wait
  //wait for all commands to finish before exiting shell

Miscellaneous options
--close file_num
--verbose
  //print out each command
--profile
  //print out timing information on commands
--abort
  //close shell
--catch N
  //abort when receiving signal N
--ignore N
  //ignore signal N
--default N
  //use default behavior for signal N
--pause
  //wait for signal
